# Both variables are optional. Unset, the client behaves exactly as before —
# same-origin '/api' and same-origin WebSocket — which is correct when the
# built client is served BY the TREK server itself (the normal self-hosted/
# Docker deployment; see build-from-sources at the repo root).
#
# Set these only for a split deployment where this client is hosted
# separately from the TREK server (e.g. this build on Vercel, the server on
# Railway/Fly/a VPS/Docker elsewhere).

# VITE_API_URL=https://your-trek-server.example.com/api
# VITE_WS_URL=wss://your-trek-server.example.com

# Whichever host runs the server also needs its ALLOWED_ORIGINS
# (server/.env.example) to include this client's deployed origin, or the
# browser's requests will be blocked by CORS.
